Migration Strategy: Docker Swarm to Kubernetes
1. Feature Mapping: Swarm to Kubernetes
Docker Swarm Feature Kubernetes Equivalent
Swarm Service (replicated) Deployment
Swarm Service (stateful) StatefulSet
Docker Secrets Kubernetes Secrets
Docker Configs ConfigMaps
Overlay Network CNI + NetworkPolicy
Placement Constraints NodeSelector / Affinity
Rolling Updates RollingUpdate Strategy
Named Volumes PersistentVolume + PVC
2. Migration Approach (Phased Strategy)
• Phase 1 – Provision Kubernetes cluster and configure ingress, storage, monitoring.
• Phase 2 – Deploy stateless services (API, frontend).
• Phase 3 – Migrate stateful services with controlled data synchronization.
• Phase 4 – DNS cutover and production validation.
3. Testing Strategy
• Functional testing of all API endpoints and services.
• Load testing to validate scaling behavior.
• Observability validation (logs, metrics, health checks).
• Blue/Green or Canary deployment validation.
4. Rollback Plan
• Use kubectl rollout undo for Kubernetes deployments.
• Switch DNS back to Swarm cluster if required.
• Restore database from backup if necessary.
5. Helm Chart Structure
